This software builds on, and is designed to interoperate with, the RootNav tools
from the University of Nottingham, both BSD-3-Clause licensed:

  RootNav 1
    Pound MP, French AP, Atkinson JA, Wells DM, Bennett MJ, Pridmore T (2013).
    "RootNav: Navigating Images of Complex Root Architectures." Plant Physiology 162:1802-1814.
    Copyright (c) 2011, The University of Nottingham. All rights reserved.
    https://www.plant-image-analysis.org/software/rootnav

  RootNav 2.0
    Yasrab R, Atkinson JA, Wells DM, French AP, Pridmore TP, Pound MP (2019).
    "RootNav 2.0: Deep learning for automatic navigation of complex plant root architectures."
    GigaScience 8(11):giz123.
    https://github.com/robail-yasrab/RootNav-2.0

The bundled model `models/arabidopsis.onnx` is the RootNav 2.0 "arabidopsis_plate" model
(HourglassNet), exported to ONNX from the weights published at
https://cvl.cs.nott.ac.uk/resources/trainedmodels/arabidopsis_plate-ea874d94.pth
  Model weights: CC-BY-4.0 (Robail Yasrab, University of Nottingham) — redistributed here
    with attribution under those terms.
  Training dataset: CC-BY-NC-4.0 (Jonathan Atkinson, Darren Wells, University of Nottingham).
Other RootNav 2.0 models exported for AstroRoot remain subject to their own upstream licence;
verify before redistributing any .onnx model.

ONNX Runtime Web (Microsoft, MIT) is loaded at runtime to execute models in the browser.

The demo/test images in `samples/images/` are web-optimized copies of the NASA ABRS
(Advanced Biological Research System) ISS root time-lapse (flight + ground control, 2010),
from https://github.com/dr-richard-barker/image-analysis-software-and-R-codes
(ABRS_NASA_Roots_TimeLapse). See Paul, Amalfitano & Ferl (2012) BMC Plant Biology 12:232.
Sample RSML in `samples/tictoc/` are from the TICTOC cotton study
(https://github.com/dr-richard-barker/TICTOC).

The demo images in `samples/images/apex03/` are web-optimized copies of APEX-03 / TAGES-ISA
ISS root plate photographs (Col-0, WS, spr1/SKU6, sku5; flight + ground control) from the same
image-analysis-software-and-R-codes repository (APEX03/). See Califar et al. (2020) "Root
Skewing-Associated Genes Impact the Spaceflight Response of Arabidopsis thaliana", Front. Plant
Sci. 11:239.
